      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3R5-cBCdgZMX"
      },
      "source": [
        "## ex. 1"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "U_TdQatDgZMZ"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$  \n",
        "y = x^Tx,  \\quad x \\in \\mathbb{R}^N \n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lZ8BJ0I802NF"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x_p}x^Tx = \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x_p}\\sum\\limits_{i=1}^n x_i^2 = 2x_p\n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "WD4cZ6i30450"
      },
      "source": [
        "Therefore, \n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dy}{dx} =  2x\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pLLR1g-CgZMd"
      },
      "source": [
        "## ex. 2"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "G759_ecLgZMd"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$ y = tr(AB) \\quad A,B \\in \\mathbb{R}^{N \\times N} $$ "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QM3ztf9E1jDM"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial a_{pq}}tr(AB) = \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial a_{pq}}\\sum\\limits_{i,j=1}^n a_{ij}b_{ji}= b_{qp} = b_{qp}\n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "helYeZkcgZMe"
      },
      "source": [
        "Therefore, \n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dy}{dA} = B^T\n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yMo31D8WgZMf"
      },
      "source": [
        "## ex. 3"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2R4vM851gZMf"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$  \n",
        "y = x^TAc , \\quad A\\in \\mathbb{R}^{N \\times N}, x\\in \\mathbb{R}^{N}, c\\in \\mathbb{R}^{N} \n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "whlO0OdG5H6L"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x_p}x^TAc = \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial x_p}(\\sum\\limits_{i=1}^n c_i \\cdot \\sum\\limits_{j=1}^n x_j a_{ji}) = \\sum\\limits_{i=1}^n c_i a_{pi}\n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "X_7fJdMRgZMg"
      },
      "source": [
        "Therefore, \n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dy}{dx} = Ac\n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Fw1jFn5Z-bbU"
      },
      "source": [
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{\\partial}{\\partial a_{pq}}x^TAc = \\frac{\\partial}{\\partial a_{pq}} (\\sum\\limits_{i=1}^n c_i \\cdot \\sum\\limits_{j=1}^n x_j a_{ji}) = x_p c_q\n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EAJ16GNggZNA"
      },
      "source": [
        "Therefore, \n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dy}{dA} = xc^T\n",
        "$$ "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EY6i2VmcgZNB"
      },
      "source": [
        "Hint for the latter (one of the ways): use *ex. 2* result and the fact \n",
        "$$\n",
        "tr(ABC) = tr (CAB)\n",
        "$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d-CTLiwjgZNC"
      },
      "source": [
        "## ex. 4"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yCbfOyiOgZND"
      },
      "source": [
        "Classic matrix factorization example. Given matrix $X$ you need to find $A$, $S$ to approximate $X$. This can be done by simple gradient descent iteratively alternating $A$ and $S$ updates.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "J = || X - AS ||_F^2  , \\quad A\\in \\mathbb{R}^{N \\times R} , \\quad S\\in \\mathbb{R}^{R \\times M}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dJ}{dS} = ? \n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "You may use one of the following approaches:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "HbU_BDHkgZNF"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### First approach\n",
        "Using ex.2 and the fact:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "|| X ||_F^2 = tr(XX^T) \n",
        "$$ \n",
        "it is easy to derive gradients (you can find it in one of the refs). "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "IPzn63nkgZNG"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### Second approach\n",
        "You can use *slightly different techniques* if they suits you. Take a look at this derivation:\n",
        "<img src=\"https://github.com/girafe-ai/ml-mipt/blob/basic_s21/homeworks_basic/Lab1_ML_pipeline_and_SVM/grad.png?raw=1\">\n",
        "(excerpt from [Handbook of blind source separation, Jutten, page 517](https://books.google.ru/books?id=PTbj03bYH6kC&printsec=frontcover&dq=Handbook+of+Blind+Source+Separation&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwi-q_apiJDLAhULvXIKHVXJDWcQ6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=Handbook%20of%20Blind%20Source%20Separation&f=false), open for better picture)."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "_cVT2u4ugZNG"
      },
      "source": [
        "#### Third approach\n",
        "And finally we can use chain rule! \n",
        "let $ F = AS $ \n",
        "\n",
        "**Find**\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dJ}{dF} =  \n",
        "$$ \n",
        "and \n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dF}{dS} =  \n",
        "$$ \n",
        "(the shape should be $ NM \\times RM )$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Now it is easy do get desired gradients:\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\frac{dJ}{dS} =  \n",
        "$$ "
      ]
